  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: eef041081aed1064791c1fe85b5ec65e, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bitdepth
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Title: Bit depth mode
  Body: '<b>8 bits per channel (8bpc)</b>


    8-bit colour and directional values.
    Good enough for most scenarios, especially additive Light Volumes.\n\nIn this
    format, the direction components for light bakes get just 256 steps across the
    full range instead of thousands, which can cause subtle banding or stair-stepping
    artefacts in light directionality. These artefacts can be noticeable on non-additive
    Light Volumes.


    -


    <b>16 bits per channel (16bpc)</b>


    16 bits
    per channel preserves subtle variations in colour and light direction, at the
    cost of being double the size of 8-bit depth.\n\nBest non-additive Light Volumes,
    and limited to small and short bakes. On additive Light Volumes the quality difference
    between this and 16bpc is pretty much imperceptible.'
  Images: []
